[src:ito-calculus/itô-s-lemma] The Poisson process model for jumps is that the probability of one jump in the interval [*t*, *t* + Δ*t*] is *h*Δ*t* plus higher order terms. h could be a constant, a deterministic function of time, or a stochastic process.
[src:ito-calculus/itô-s-lemma] The survival probability *ps*(*t*) is the probability that no jump has occurred in the interval [0, *t*].
[src:ito-calculus/itô-s-lemma] Let *S*(*t*) be a discontinuous stochastic process.
